00:28:28.400 --> 00:28:34.400
felt super satisfied to solve, which absolutely made no sense to us.

464
00:28:34.400 --> 00:28:36.400
Because...

465
00:28:47.400 --> 00:28:48.400
That's a good picture.

466
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:50.400
Yeah, I know, it's a good picture.

467
00:28:50.760 --> 00:28:54.760
Portal 2 is just going to be this picture over and over again.

468
00:28:57.760 --> 00:29:01.760
When it comes right down to it, at that point in the game, that's about the easiest puzzle

469
00:29:01.760 --> 00:29:02.760
in Portal.

470
00:29:02.760 --> 00:29:07.760
You place a portal on the wall next to the fire pit, and then you place one in a safe

471
00:29:07.760 --> 00:29:09.760
area, and you just hop through it.

472
00:29:09.760 --> 00:29:11.760
That's it.

473
00:29:11.760 --> 00:29:18.760
So, we then had to sit down and reflect, like, what in the world made this so climactic?

474
00:29:19.120 --> 00:29:22.120
And one of the things that we learned was that, well, it had time pressure.

475
00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:25.120
You know, there was only a limited amount of time while you were on that platform before

476
00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:29.120
you were going to get burned alive to place your portals and escape.

477
00:29:29.120 --> 00:29:34.120
And, you know, as I think I've said before, time pressure makes people think something

478
00:29:34.120 --> 00:29:38.120
that is a lot more complicated than it actually is.

479
00:29:38.120 --> 00:29:41.120
Another thing was it had a really high visual impact.

480
00:29:41.120 --> 00:29:45.120
I mean, you can't really go wrong with a platform heading straight into a giant pit of fire

481
00:29:45.120 --> 00:29:47.120
for visual impact.

482
00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:50.480
But, you know, it's something that our players had never seen before in the game, and so

483
00:29:50.480 --> 00:29:52.480
it was, you know, something new.

484
00:29:52.480 --> 00:29:58.480
There's also a dramatic high point, because for the first time, GLaDOS is pretty openly

485
00:29:58.480 --> 00:30:02.480
trying to kill you, and also for the first time, you're able to assert a little bit of

486
00:30:02.480 --> 00:30:05.480
control over your environment and escape from her.

487
00:30:05.480 --> 00:30:11.480
And, like Kim was saying, all of those three things combined made it so that an easy puzzle

488
00:30:11.840 --> 00:30:18.840
was sort of feeling like a much more complicated puzzle, which allowed us, led us to the realization

489
00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:22.840
that we'd been holding onto this idea that we needed a complex puzzle at the end, and

490
00:30:22.840 --> 00:30:25.840
it simply just wasn't true.

491
00:30:25.840 --> 00:30:28.840
So here's what we actually shipped in the game as boss battle.

492
00:30:28.840 --> 00:30:33.840
You can see GLaDOS there with her little personality spheres, and then next to her was a hatch

493
00:30:33.840 --> 00:30:37.840
where a rocket launcher would pop up, and you'd have to reorient the rockets and hit

494
00:30:38.200 --> 00:30:44.200
GLaDOS, take one of those spheres, and then put it in the incinerator by, you know, getting

495
00:30:44.200 --> 00:30:49.200
to the activation switch with your portals, and then getting back to the incinerator and

496
00:30:49.200 --> 00:30:50.200
tossing it in.

497
00:30:50.200 --> 00:30:51.200
The end.

498
00:30:51.200 --> 00:30:52.200
Done.

499
00:30:52.200 --> 00:30:57.200
So, taking the four lessons we learned, this is how we applied them to the final GLaDOS

500
00:30:57.200 --> 00:30:58.200
battle.

501
00:30:58.200 --> 00:30:59.200
First of all was time pressure.

502
00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:04.200
We were ourselves under some time pressure, so instead of getting fancy, we actually just

503
00:31:04.200 --> 00:31:07.200
had a timer counting down to something that would kill you.

504
00:31:07.560 --> 00:31:11.560
And we decided that thing that would kill you would be some neurotoxin, because it was

505
00:31:11.560 --> 00:31:14.560
also really cheap just to make a green particle system.

506
00:31:17.560 --> 00:31:18.560
You laugh, but it's seriously true.

507
00:31:18.560 --> 00:31:20.560
Yeah, that's 100% true.

508
00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:23.560
So, you know, visual impact.

509
00:31:23.560 --> 00:31:27.560
Well, on one side of the screen, you know, on the far side over there, you can see a

