00:31:27.560 --> 00:31:31.560
piece of concept art that an artist at Valve, Jason Braschel, did for us.

511
00:31:31.560 --> 00:31:32.560
Thanks, Jason.

512
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:35.560
And on the other side there, you can see what we actually shipped.

513
00:31:35.920 --> 00:31:38.920
So everything in this room, visually, is pointing at GLaDOS.

514
00:31:38.920 --> 00:31:42.920
You know, got the geometry of the stairs leading up to her, got all the lights pointing at

515
00:31:42.920 --> 00:31:43.920
her.

516
00:31:43.920 --> 00:31:48.920
You know, after all this time of hearing GLaDOS heckle you and harass you, you know, we wanted

517
00:31:48.920 --> 00:31:50.920
to make this room have some serious impact.

518
00:31:50.920 --> 00:31:54.920
And, you know, I think it did its job pretty well.

519
00:31:54.920 --> 00:31:58.920
And, you know, it's not like any other room in the game, and so I think it really gave

520
00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:00.920
players a sense of satisfaction.

521
00:32:01.280 --> 00:32:08.280
And then in terms of a high dramatic moment, putting some time pressure to the puzzle made

522
00:32:08.280 --> 00:32:14.280
it so that I only had to write like six minutes of decent dialogue, which is in stark contrast

523
00:32:14.280 --> 00:32:20.280
to all our previous attempts, which required me to write infinity minutes of excellent

524
00:32:20.280 --> 00:32:21.280
dialogue.

525
00:32:21.280 --> 00:32:23.280
Which makes Eric crack.

526
00:32:23.280 --> 00:32:27.280
That was a bad time for me, writing infinity minutes of dialogue.

527
00:32:27.640 --> 00:32:30.640
And finally, the easy puzzle.

528
00:32:30.640 --> 00:32:34.640
You know, when all is said and done, Portal is a puzzle game.

529
00:32:34.640 --> 00:32:39.640
But all the things that we learned led us back towards, you know, we need to simplify

530
00:32:39.640 --> 00:32:40.640
this puzzle.

531
00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:44.640
So adding time pressure and then, you know, having it be a very dramatic room and have

532
00:32:44.640 --> 00:32:47.640
a lot of really interesting points made by GLaDOS.

533
00:32:47.640 --> 00:32:52.640
Scaling back the puzzle allowed players to really absorb this moment and have a good

